1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,700
This is ridiculous.

2
00:00:04,700 --> 00:00:06,700
I had tickets to see Tom Petty.

3
00:00:06,700 --> 00:00:09,700
Well Friday nights are the nights that I pick up my outfits are Saturday nights.

4
00:00:09,700 --> 00:00:12,700
Well I had to give the tickets to my ex-wife.

5
00:00:12,700 --> 00:00:14,700
Or boyfriend.

6
00:00:14,700 --> 00:00:16,700
Took a big loss.

7
00:00:16,700 --> 00:00:19,700
Not that anybody cares.

8
00:00:19,700 --> 00:00:23,700
There's a perception out there that working in the paper industry is glamorous.

9
00:00:23,700 --> 00:00:26,700
But here's what the media doesn't show you.

10
00:00:26,700 --> 00:00:29,700
Sometimes we have to stay late on a Friday night.

11
00:00:30,400 --> 00:00:32,400
Did I just blow your mind?

12
00:00:32,400 --> 00:00:35,400
Do you have any idea what time we'll get out of here?

13
00:00:35,400 --> 00:00:37,400
Nobody likes to work late.

14
00:00:37,400 --> 00:00:39,400
At least of all me.

15
00:00:39,400 --> 00:00:41,400
Do you have plans tonight?

16
00:00:41,400 --> 00:00:43,400
No I don't.

17
00:00:43,400 --> 00:00:45,400
Remember when you told us not to make plans because we were working?

18
00:00:45,400 --> 00:00:47,400
Yes I remember.

19
00:00:47,400 --> 00:00:49,400
Mmm this is BS.

20
00:00:49,400 --> 00:00:51,400
This is BS. Why are we here?

21
00:00:51,400 --> 00:00:53,400
I am going to call corporate.

22
00:00:53,400 --> 00:00:55,400
Enough is enough.

23
00:00:55,400 --> 00:00:57,400
I'm Scott. I'm so mad.

24
00:00:57,400 --> 00:00:59,400
This is Michael Scott.

25
00:01:00,100 --> 00:01:02,100
Well we don't want to work.

26
00:01:02,100 --> 00:01:04,100
No we don't.

27
00:01:04,100 --> 00:01:06,100
It's not fair to these people.

28
00:01:06,100 --> 00:01:09,100
These people are my friends and I care about them.

29
00:01:09,100 --> 00:01:11,100
We're not going to do it.

30
00:01:13,100 --> 00:01:15,100
Everybody I just got off the horn with corporate.

31
00:01:15,100 --> 00:01:21,100
And basically I told them where they could stick their little overtime assignment.

32
00:01:21,100 --> 00:01:23,100
Go enjoy your Friday.

33
00:01:23,100 --> 00:01:25,100
Thank you Michael.

34
00:01:25,100 --> 00:01:27,100
Well I think we dodged a bullet there.

35
00:01:27,100 --> 00:01:29,100
I think we should celebrate.

36
00:01:29,800 --> 00:01:31,800
You, Pam, me, Casa, little dinner dancing drinks.

37
00:01:31,800 --> 00:01:33,800
You said you didn't have plans.

38
00:01:35,800 --> 00:01:37,800
That's what you said.

39
00:01:37,800 --> 00:01:41,800
Michael has asked Pam and me to dinner at least nine times.

40
00:01:41,800 --> 00:01:43,800
And every time we've been able to get out of it.

41
00:01:43,800 --> 00:01:45,800
But I got to give him credit.

42
00:01:45,800 --> 00:01:47,800
He got me.

43
00:01:47,800 --> 00:01:53,800
Because I'm starting to suspect that there was no assignment from corporate.

44
00:01:53,800 --> 00:01:55,800
Michael, what time should I be arriving?

45
00:01:55,800 --> 00:01:57,800
Dwight is couples only.

46
00:01:58,500 --> 00:02:00,500
And besides I only have six wine glasses.

47
00:02:00,500 --> 00:02:02,500
So it will be me and Jan and Pam and Jim.

48
00:02:02,500 --> 00:02:04,500
And Angela and Andy.

49
00:02:04,500 --> 00:02:06,500
Heyo!

50
00:02:08,500 --> 00:02:10,500
Does it bother me that I wasn't invited to Michael's dinner party?

51
00:02:18,500 --> 00:02:20,500
My ideal dinner party. Easy.

52
00:02:20,500 --> 00:02:26,500
Jim Pam, Ryan, the mayor, Barack Obama, Shiloh Jolie Pitt,

53
00:02:27,200 --> 00:02:31,200
because at the end of the night Brad or Angelina would have to come and pick him up.

54
00:02:31,200 --> 00:02:33,200
And I would get to meet them.

55
00:02:33,200 --> 00:02:37,200
Shiloh Beef, because of Disturbia.

56
00:02:37,200 --> 00:02:41,200
All of the children of the world.

57
00:02:41,200 --> 00:02:45,200
Val Kilmer, but he probably wouldn't come.

58
00:02:45,200 --> 00:02:47,200
Too famous.

59
00:02:47,200 --> 00:02:49,200
Obviously George Clooney.

60
00:02:51,200 --> 00:02:53,200
And Jan, definitely.

61
00:02:53,200 --> 00:02:55,200
If there was room.

62
00:02:55,900 --> 00:02:57,900
It is really hard when you mess with this schedule like that.

63
00:02:57,900 --> 00:02:59,900
I hate to see Tom Petty.

64
00:02:59,900 --> 00:03:01,900
Well I'm sure the heartbreakers will be heartbroken.

65
00:03:05,900 --> 00:03:07,900
No one even heard me.

66
00:03:07,900 --> 00:03:09,900
I'll tell you about my ideal dinner party.

67
00:03:09,900 --> 00:03:17,900
John Wilkes Booth, Lee Harvey Oswald, Osama Bin Laden, John Wayne Gacy, and Jeffrey Lionel Dahmer.

68
00:03:17,900 --> 00:03:19,900
Oh, hey guys, welcome to my home.

69
00:03:19,900 --> 00:03:21,900
Oh, here comes the waiter with the soup.

70
00:03:21,900 --> 00:03:23,900
Hope you guys are hungry.

71
00:03:24,600 --> 00:03:26,600
Meanwhile, the waiter subtly nods at me.

72
00:03:26,600 --> 00:03:28,600
But I don't acknowledge him.

73
00:03:28,600 --> 00:03:30,600
But I know he's an assassin, because I trained him.

74
00:03:30,600 --> 00:03:34,600
Boom, two minutes later, five dead psychopaths at my dining room table.

75
00:03:34,600 --> 00:03:36,600
All that's left to do is dispose of the bodies and collect the reward.

76
00:03:36,600 --> 00:03:38,600
It's almost too easy.

77
00:03:54,600 --> 00:03:56,600
A few hours later.

78
00:04:18,600 --> 00:04:20,600
We can turn back, it's not too late.

79
00:04:20,600 --> 00:04:22,600
We eat and we're out.

80
00:04:23,300 --> 00:04:25,300
We have to wake up early tomorrow.

81
00:04:25,300 --> 00:04:29,300
Yes, because it is Saturday.

82
00:04:29,300 --> 00:04:31,300
Hi!

83
00:04:31,300 --> 00:04:33,300
Hello! How are you?

84
00:04:33,300 --> 00:04:35,300
Come on in. Good to see you.

85
00:04:35,300 --> 00:04:39,300
I'm so glad we finally got to do this with you guys.

86
00:04:39,300 --> 00:04:43,300
You want to take their coats, baby?

87
00:04:43,300 --> 00:04:45,300
Yes, I would.

88
00:04:45,300 --> 00:04:47,300
So, what have you been doing?

89
00:04:47,300 --> 00:04:49,300
Let's see, since I saw you an hour ago?

90
00:04:49,300 --> 00:04:51,300
Yeah, I have been getting ready.

91
00:04:52,000 --> 00:04:54,000
And then driving over here.

92
00:04:54,000 --> 00:04:56,000
Well, we've been doing pretty much the same thing.

93
00:04:56,000 --> 00:04:58,000
Except driving.

94
00:04:58,000 --> 00:05:00,000
We got you this.

95
00:05:00,000 --> 00:05:02,000
Oh, well Pam, thank you.

96
00:05:02,000 --> 00:05:04,000
This will be great to cook with.

97
00:05:04,000 --> 00:05:06,000
We'll have a seat, or come on in, or I don't know.

98
00:05:06,000 --> 00:05:08,000
Make yourself to home.

99
00:05:08,000 --> 00:05:10,000
This is our casa.

100
00:05:10,000 --> 00:05:12,000
Really nice.

101
00:05:12,000 --> 00:05:14,000
So what do you guys think? Should we do the tour first?

102
00:05:14,000 --> 00:05:16,000
Do we have appetizers first?

103
00:05:16,000 --> 00:05:18,000
Tour. Let's do the tour first.

104
00:05:18,000 --> 00:05:20,000
You have preference, babe? Upstairs first?

105
00:05:20,000 --> 00:05:22,000
Totally your call, babe.

106
00:05:22,000 --> 00:05:24,000
Alright, well, let's go then. I'd sneak upstairs.

107
00:05:24,000 --> 00:05:26,000
Oh.

108
00:05:26,000 --> 00:05:28,000
You guys doing a little construction?

109
00:05:28,000 --> 00:05:30,000
Oh, just redoing the sliding glass door.

110
00:05:30,000 --> 00:05:32,000
Yeah, so sorry about this god awful carpet.

111
00:05:32,000 --> 00:05:34,000
We are still a work in progress here.
